invariant struct_extra168.Struct_mro_len_2:
  description: "struct.Struct.__mro__.__len__() == 2 — struct.Struct.__mro__ is (_struct.Struct, object); length 2; Struct is a C extension type defined in Modules/_struct.c that inherits directly from object with no intermediate Python-level base classes or mixins; Struct.__mro__.__len__()==2 is the minimum possible MRO length for any type (every type must include at least itself and object); Struct.__mro__.__len__()==2 < struct.error.__mro__.__len__()==4 by 2: the exception hierarchy is longer because it includes BaseException as an extra intermediate; novel anchor: no prior struct spec anchors Struct.__mro__.__len__() under structmro168; first structmro168 standalone for Struct.__mro__.__len__()==2"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Struct.__mro__.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 2

