invariant struct_extra168.error_mro_len_4:
  description: "struct.error.__mro__.__len__() == 4 — struct.error.__mro__ is (struct.error, Exception, BaseException, object); length 4; struct.error inherits from Exception (for regular error handling), which inherits from BaseException (the root of all Python exceptions), which inherits from object; the 4-class MRO follows the standard exception hierarchy: class > Exception > BaseException > object; struct.error.__mro__.__len__()==4 > Struct.__mro__.__len__()==2 by 2: exceptions have longer MROs than plain types because of the exception class hierarchy; novel anchor: no prior struct spec anchors error.__mro__.__len__() under structmro168; first structmro168 standalone for struct.error.__mro__.__len__()==4"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: error.__mro__.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 4

